headlines.description: — Joel Embiid showed again Tuesday night why he believes he deserves this season's MVP Award.
headlines.shortLinkText: Embiid scores 45, 76ers beat Pacers to pull even in Atlantic

headlines.description: — The Cleveland Cavaliers gave up 120 points to one of the NBA's most offensively challenged teams Tuesday night and took a loss that locked them into the Eastern Conference play-in tournament.
headlines.shortLinkText: Magic break 6-game losing streak, beat Cavaliers 120-115

headlines.description: — Kyrie Irving scored 42 points and the Brooklyn Nets beat the Houston Rockets 118-105 on Tuesday night to improve their position in the race for play-in seeding.
headlines.shortLinkText: Irving scores 42, Nets beat Rockets 118-105 to move to 8th

headlines.description: — Tyler Herro scored 35 points off the bench and the Miami Heat moved closer to clinching the No. 1 seed in the Eastern Conference playoffs with a 144-115 victory over the Charlotte Hornets on Tuesday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Herro scores 35, Heat beat Hornets 144-115 for 5th straight

headlines.description: — Pascal Siakam had 31 points and 13 rebounds, Scottie Barnes added 19 points and 14 rebounds, and the Toronto Raptors clinched a playoff berth by beating the Atlanta Hawks 118-108 on Tuesday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Siakam has 31 as Raptors beat Hawks to clinch playoff spot

headlines.description: — Giannis Antetokounmpo didn't dominate the way he usually does.
headlines.shortLinkText: Lopez scores 28, Bucks beat Bulls 127-106 to clinch Central

headlines.description: — Kristaps Porzingis scored 25 points, including 12 in the third quarter as Washington took control, and the Wizards pulled away for a 132-114 win against the Minnesota Timberwolves on Tuesday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Porzingis scores 25, Wizards cruise to win over Timberwolves

events.name: Portland Trail Blazers at Oklahoma City Thunder

headlines.description: — Jaylen Hoard had career highs of 24 points and 21 rebounds to help the Oklahoma City Thunder top the Portland Trail Blazers 98-94 on Tuesday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Hoard's 24 points, 21 rebounds lift Thunder past Portland

events.name: San Antonio Spurs at Denver Nuggets

headlines.description: — Devin Vassell and Keldon Johnson each scored 20 points to help the San Antonio Spurs secure a spot in the play-in tournament Tuesday night following a 116-97 victory over the Denver Nuggets.
headlines.shortLinkText: Spurs beat Nuggets 116-97, earn spot in play-in tournament

headlines.description: — Rudy Gobert had 22 points and 21 rebounds, and the Utah Jazz clinched a playoff berth with a 121-115 overtime victory over the Memphis Grizzlies on Tuesday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Jazz clinch playoff spot with 121-115 OT win over Grizzlies

events.name: New Orleans Pelicans at Sacramento Kings
Los Angeles Lakers at Phoenix Suns

headlines.description: — The shots kept falling for Devin Booker, who appeared he was trying to prove a point.
headlines.shortLinkText: Booker scores 32, Suns eliminate Lakers from playoff race
